              <span slot="content">The music and choreography are stunning! The first three or four times. Then they become repetitive, and frankly, kind of dull. 

And the storytelling is very weak. There are so many holes in the first half I dont quite know where to start—well, how about what actually drew Ann to the Shaking Quakers? How did their spiritual practices speak to her life? Seemed totally random to me. And why on Earth did people listen to her? I like Amanda Seyfried, but I wouldnt have followed her to the backyard. 

Then theres the problem of the voice over narrative. Pretty much always a bad idea, but with a thick and inconsistent accent, just no. And having Sister Mary tell us the story before it was played out robbed the actual scenes of dramatic power. 

The second half of the movie was very by-the-book. No sec. You want to have sex? Leave the movement. Was this supposed to be a surprise? We need followers. Okay, here are followers. People will hate you? Now well show people hating the Shakers. Im sorry, I just dont think theres much here.</span>
